<p>Elegant with beautiful, subtle textures. Joan has a way of creating the dreamiest collages.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://sarahschulte.studio/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sarah Schulte</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781620979556" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263963" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/alain-mabanckou-dealing-with-the-dead/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alain-Mabanckou-Dealing-With-the-Dead.jpg" data-orig-size="971,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Alain Mabanckou, Dealing With the Dead" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Alain Mabanckou, &lt;em&gt;Dealing With the Dead&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Jack Smyth (New Press, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alain-Mabanckou-Dealing-With-the-Dead-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alain-Mabanckou-Dealing-With-the-Dead-663x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263963" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alain-Mabanckou-Dealing-With-the-Dead.jpg" alt="" width="971" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alain-Mabanckou-Dealing-With-the-Dead.jpg 971w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alain-Mabanckou-Dealing-With-the-Dead-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alain-Mabanckou-Dealing-With-the-Dead-663x1024.jpg 663w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alain-Mabanckou-Dealing-With-the-Dead-768x1186.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alain-Mabanckou-Dealing-With-the-Dead-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Alain-Mabanckou-Dealing-With-the-Dead-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 971px) 100vw, 971px" /></a> Alain Mabanckou, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781620979556" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Dealing With the Dead</a></em>; cover design by Jack Smyth (New Press, September)</span>
<p>How do all of these colors work so well together?! An otherwise simple composition sings to life with a few lively border treatments and a sumptuous palette. Jack&#8217;s alchemy here makes me wish it was a series.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jasonarias.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jason Arias</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255732" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/what-hunger-9781668065570_hr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/what-hunger-9781668065570_hr.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2146" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Catherine Dang, What Hunger" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Catherine Dang, What Hunger; cover design by Maddy Angstreich; photograph by Bobby Doherty (Simon &#038; Schuster, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/what-hunger-9781668065570_hr-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/what-hunger-9781668065570_hr-668x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-255732" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/what-hunger-9781668065570_hr.jpg" alt="Catherine Dang, What Hunger" width="1400" height="2146" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/what-hunger-9781668065570_hr.jpg 1400w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/what-hunger-9781668065570_hr-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/what-hunger-9781668065570_hr-668x1024.jpg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/what-hunger-9781668065570_hr-768x1177.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/what-hunger-9781668065570_hr-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/what-hunger-9781668065570_hr-1002x1536.jpg 1002w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/what-hunger-9781668065570_hr-1336x2048.jpg 1336w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/what-hunger-9781668065570_hr-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px" /> Catherine Dang, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668065570" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>What Hunger</em></a>; cover design by Maddy Angstreich; photograph by Bobby Doherty (Simon &amp; Schuster, August)</span>
<p>Visceral and tactile, this oversized cover pulls you in with almost carnal intensity.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://cb-smith.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Coralie Bickford-Smith</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263907" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/design-harder-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/design-harder-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="876,1366" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="design harder copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Erik Carter, &lt;em&gt;Design Harder&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by No Ideas Studio (Book Ideas, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/design-harder-copy-192x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/design-harder-copy-657x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263907" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/design-harder-copy.jpg" alt="" width="876" height="1366" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/design-harder-copy.jpg 876w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/design-harder-copy-192x300.jpg 192w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/design-harder-copy-657x1024.jpg 657w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/design-harder-copy-768x1198.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/design-harder-copy-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/design-harder-copy-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 876px) 100vw, 876px" /> Erik Carter, <em>Design Harder</em>; cover design by No Ideas Studio (Book Ideas, October)</span>
<p>Maybe intentionally, I find the case material off-putting and unpleasant to hold, but Wei Hung’s Common Serif stroked until it almost loses legibility, the filled-in counters and glyphs running into each other, amplified by the debossed stamped matte black pigment is beautiful.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://owencorrigan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Owen Corrigan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238830" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263864" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/wax-child-uk/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/wax-child-uk.jpg" data-orig-size="1559,2409" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="wax child uk" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Olga Ravn, tr. Martin Aitken, &lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238830&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Wax Child&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Dan Jackson (Viking, November) **&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/wax-child-uk-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/wax-child-uk-663x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263864" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/wax-child-uk.jpg" alt="" width="1559" height="2409" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/wax-child-uk.jpg 1559w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/wax-child-uk-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/wax-child-uk-663x1024.jpg 663w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/wax-child-uk-768x1187.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/wax-child-uk-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/wax-child-uk-994x1536.jpg 994w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/wax-child-uk-1325x2048.jpg 1325w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/wax-child-uk-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1559px) 100vw, 1559px" /></a> Olga Ravn, tr. Martin Aitken, <a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238830" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Wax Child</em></a>; cover design by Dan Jackson (Viking UK, November)</span>
<p>I love all of Olga Ravn’s covers and can’t pick between the US and UK covers for this book. They are both so good. I love the solemn engraving here. And the decision to use only one pop of colour.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.katesinclair.space/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kate Sinclair</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781838957292" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264051" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/johan-norberg-peak-human/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Johan-Norberg-Peak-Human.jpg" data-orig-size="1014,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Johan Norberg, Peak Human" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Johan Norberg, &lt;em&gt;Peak Human&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by  Steve Leard (Atlantic Books, September) **&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Johan-Norberg-Peak-Human-203x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Johan-Norberg-Peak-Human-692x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264051" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Johan-Norberg-Peak-Human.jpg" alt="" width="1014" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Johan-Norberg-Peak-Human.jpg 1014w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Johan-Norberg-Peak-Human-203x300.jpg 203w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Johan-Norberg-Peak-Human-692x1024.jpg 692w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Johan-Norberg-Peak-Human-768x1136.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Johan-Norberg-Peak-Human-41x60.jpg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Johan-Norberg-Peak-Human-34x50.jpg 34w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1014px) 100vw, 1014px" /></a> Johan Norberg, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781838957292" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Peak Human</a></em>; cover design by Steve Leard (Atlantic Books, September)</span>
<p>Perfect combination of title and art. Simple and to the point.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jamesiacobelli.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">James Iacobelli</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9798888903681" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263029" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/100-notable-small-press-books-of-2025/theory-of-water-nishnaabe-maps-to-the-times-ahead/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Theory-of-Water-Nishnaabe-Maps-to-the-Times-Ahead.jpg" data-orig-size="800,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Theory of Water- Nishnaabe Maps to the Times Ahead" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Leanne Betasamosake Simpson, &lt;em&gt;Theory of Water&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Kelly Hill (Haymarket, April)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Theory-of-Water-Nishnaabe-Maps-to-the-Times-Ahead-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Theory-of-Water-Nishnaabe-Maps-to-the-Times-Ahead-683x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263029" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Theory-of-Water-Nishnaabe-Maps-to-the-Times-Ahead.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="1200" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Theory-of-Water-Nishnaabe-Maps-to-the-Times-Ahead.jpg 800w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Theory-of-Water-Nishnaabe-Maps-to-the-Times-Ahead-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Theory-of-Water-Nishnaabe-Maps-to-the-Times-Ahead-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Theory-of-Water-Nishnaabe-Maps-to-the-Times-Ahead-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Theory-of-Water-Nishnaabe-Maps-to-the-Times-Ahead-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Theory-of-Water-Nishnaabe-Maps-to-the-Times-Ahead-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></a> Leanne Betasamosake Simpson, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9798888903681" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Theory of Water</a></em>; cover design by Kelly Hill (Haymarket, April)</span>
<p>Gorgeous texture and movement that so effortlessly reflects the writing within.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.morgankrehbiel.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Morgan Krehbiel</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374613204" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="259827" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/behind-the-fame-and-inspirations-of-muriel-spark/electric-spark/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/electric-spark-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1707,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="electric spark" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Frances Wilson, &lt;em&gt;Electric Spark&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Tom Etherington (FSG, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/electric-spark-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/electric-spark-683x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-259827" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/electric-spark-scaled.jpg" alt="" width="1707" height="2560" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/electric-spark-scaled.jpg 1707w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/electric-spark-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/electric-spark-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/electric-spark-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/electric-spark-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/electric-spark-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/electric-spark-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/electric-spark-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1707px) 100vw, 1707px" /></a> Frances Wilson, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374613204" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Electric Spark</em></a>; cover design by Tom Etherington (FSG, September)</span>
<p>Only Tom Etherington could create something this spare and somehow also serve a level of sophisticated allure none of the rest of us knew existed.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://albanfischerdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alban Fischer</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374604165" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="247203" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/fernando-a-flores-brother-bronte/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fernando-A.-Flores-Brother-Bronte-.jpeg" data-orig-size="652,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Fernando A. Flores, Brother Brontë" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Fernando A. Flores, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374604165&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Brother Brontë&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design and art by Na Kim (MCD, February)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fernando-A.-Flores-Brother-Bronte--196x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fernando-A.-Flores-Brother-Bronte-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-247203" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fernando-A.-Flores-Brother-Bronte-.jpeg" alt="Fernando A. Flores, Brother Brontë" width="652" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fernando-A.-Flores-Brother-Bronte-.jpeg 652w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fernando-A.-Flores-Brother-Bronte--196x300.jpeg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fernando-A.-Flores-Brother-Bronte--39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Fernando-A.-Flores-Brother-Bronte--33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 652px) 100vw, 652px" /></a> Fernando A. Flores, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374604165" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Brother Brontë</em></a>; cover design and art by Na Kim (MCD, February)</span>
<p>Na&#8217;s illustrations are often the stars of her cover designs but I really enjoyed the bolder paintings she incorporated into her work this year including this one, which feels rightfully dystopian and tactile with the thicker paint strokes, inviting eyes and each element providing so much depth to the composition.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.nicolecaputo.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Nicole Caputo</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781399728843" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263869" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/81uofnxvvll-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81UoFNxvVLL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="621,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="81UoFNxvVLL._AC_UF1000,1000_QL80_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Michael Morpurgo, &lt;em&gt;Spring&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Holly Ovenden (Hodder Press, March)**&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81UoFNxvVLL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-186x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81UoFNxvVLL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263869" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81UoFNxvVLL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="" width="621" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81UoFNxvVLL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 621w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81UoFNxvVLL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-186x300.jpg 186w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81UoFNxvVLL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-37x60.jpg 37w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81UoFNxvVLL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-31x50.jpg 31w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 621px) 100vw, 621px" /></a> Michael Morpurgo, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781399728843" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Spring</a></em>; cover design by Holly Ovenden (Hodder Press, March)</span>
<p>When I saw this book in person, I was struck by its beauty. The vibrant green, gold foil, and luscious illustration is so lovely.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kelly-winton.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kelly Winton</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668087862" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255933" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/herculine-9781668087862_hr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/herculine-9781668087862_hr.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2146" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Grace Byron, Herculine" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Grace Byron, &lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668087862&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Herculine&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Ella Laytham; illustration by Evangeline Gallagher (S&amp;amp;S/Saga Press, October)&lt;/p&gt;
