<p>Love the simplicity and busyness.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jayamiceli.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jaya Miceli</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668081211" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263801" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/one-yellow-eye-uk-design-kieryn-tyler/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/one-yellow-eye-UK-design-kieryn-tyler.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,1823" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="one-yellow-eye-UK-design-kieryn-tyler" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Leigh Radford, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668081211&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;One Yellow Eye&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Kieryn Tyler (Tor Nightfire) **&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/one-yellow-eye-UK-design-kieryn-tyler-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/one-yellow-eye-UK-design-kieryn-tyler-674x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263801" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/one-yellow-eye-UK-design-kieryn-tyler.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="1823" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/one-yellow-eye-UK-design-kieryn-tyler.jpg 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/one-yellow-eye-UK-design-kieryn-tyler-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/one-yellow-eye-UK-design-kieryn-tyler-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/one-yellow-eye-UK-design-kieryn-tyler-768x1167.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/one-yellow-eye-UK-design-kieryn-tyler-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/one-yellow-eye-UK-design-kieryn-tyler-1011x1536.jpg 1011w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/one-yellow-eye-UK-design-kieryn-tyler-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></a> Leigh Radford, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668081211" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">One Yellow Eye</a></em>; cover design by Kieryn Tyler (Tor Nightfire, July)</span>
<p>The cover world is full of botched attempts to visualize a book’s title in such starkly literal terms. Kieryn’s succeeds where many have not.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://chasematt.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Matt Chase</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374613891" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264023" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/81qobelv1cl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81qOBelv1cL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="919,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="81qOBelv1cL._SL1500_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Brittany Newell, &lt;em&gt;Soft Core&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Jo Thompson, illustration by Kelly Vance (Fourth Estate, February)&lt;/p&gt;
