<p>Vibrant and surreal.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.instagram.com/jennycarrow_covers/?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jenny Carrow</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593237144" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="251204" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-13-best-book-covers-of-march/61ruvehlr8l-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/61RuvEHLR8L._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="994,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="There is No Place for Us: Working and Homeless in America" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Brian Goldstone, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593237144&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;There is No Place for Us: Working and Homeless in America&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Anna Kochman (Crown, March 25)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/61RuvEHLR8L._SL1500_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/61RuvEHLR8L._SL1500_-679x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-251204" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/61RuvEHLR8L._SL1500_.jpg" alt="There is No Place for Us: Working and Homeless in America" width="994" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/61RuvEHLR8L._SL1500_.jpg 994w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/61RuvEHLR8L._SL1500_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/61RuvEHLR8L._SL1500_-679x1024.jpg 679w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/61RuvEHLR8L._SL1500_-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/61RuvEHLR8L._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/61RuvEHLR8L._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 994px) 100vw, 994px" /></a> Brian Goldstone, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593237144" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">There is No Place for Us: Working and Homeless in America</a></em>; cover design by Anna Kochman (Crown, March 25)</span>
<p>Striking. The minimalism is so impactful, the perfect cover for this book.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://dana-li.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Dana Li</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593718773" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264056" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/helen-oyeyemi-a-new-new-me/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Helen-Oyeyemi-A-New-New-Me.jpg" data-orig-size="994,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Helen Oyeyemi, A New New Me" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Helen Oyeyemi, &lt;em&gt;A New New Me&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Lauren Peters-Collaer (Riverhead, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Helen-Oyeyemi-A-New-New-Me-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Helen-Oyeyemi-A-New-New-Me-679x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264056" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Helen-Oyeyemi-A-New-New-Me.jpg" alt="" width="994" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Helen-Oyeyemi-A-New-New-Me.jpg 994w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Helen-Oyeyemi-A-New-New-Me-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Helen-Oyeyemi-A-New-New-Me-679x1024.jpg 679w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Helen-Oyeyemi-A-New-New-Me-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Helen-Oyeyemi-A-New-New-Me-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Helen-Oyeyemi-A-New-New-Me-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 994px) 100vw, 994px" /></a> Helen Oyeyemi, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593718773" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">A New New Me</a></em>; cover design by Lauren Peters-Collaer (Riverhead, August)</span>
<p>Given the protagonist’s multiple personality disorder, a fine china cup stack is a perfect metaphor for an extreme case of imposter syndrome. I love the tension of Peters-Collaer’s type pairing and the choice to bathe the tea party in technicolor; it gives cyber-gentile vibes.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://charlottestrick.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Charlotte Strick</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9798893380309" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264062" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/51qhxcqni7l-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/51QhxCqni7L._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="984,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="51QhxCqni7L._SL1500_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Jacqueline Harpman, tr. Ros Schwartz , &lt;em&gt;I Who Have Never Known Men&lt;/em&gt; (Collector&#8217;s Edition); cover design by Justin Carder (Transit Books, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/51QhxCqni7L._SL1500_-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/51QhxCqni7L._SL1500_-672x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264062" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/51QhxCqni7L._SL1500_.jpg" alt="" width="984" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/51QhxCqni7L._SL1500_.jpg 984w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/51QhxCqni7L._SL1500_-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/51QhxCqni7L._SL1500_-672x1024.jpg 672w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/51QhxCqni7L._SL1500_-768x1171.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/51QhxCqni7L._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/51QhxCqni7L._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 984px) 100vw, 984px" /></a> Jacqueline Harpman, tr. Ros Schwartz , <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9798893380309" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">I Who Have Never Known Men</a></em> (Collector&#8217;s Edition); cover design by Justin Carder (Transit Books, September)</span>
<p>I might be partial to this book as I picked it up due to the 2022 cover, and loved it. An ethereal and minimal design, which the 2025 Collector’s Edition repurposes, titlelessly (on the front) and even more minimally, along with a snippet of the text, debossed in silver foil on the case. Neat.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markitup.xyz/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593715949" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255742" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/attachment/221754279/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/221754279.jpg" data-orig-size="993,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Kate Riley, Ruth" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Kate Riley, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593715949&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Ruth&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Lauren Peters-Collaer; art by Eugène Joseph Verboeckhoven (Riverhead, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/221754279-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/221754279-678x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-255742" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/221754279.jpg" alt="Kate Riley, Ruth" width="993" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/221754279.jpg 993w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/221754279-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/221754279-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/221754279-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/221754279-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/221754279-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 993px) 100vw, 993px" /></a> Kate Riley, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593715949" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Ruth</a></em>; cover design by Lauren Peters-Collaer; art by Eugène Joseph Verboeckhoven (Riverhead, August)</span>
<p>This crop is magnificent (both image and title). It draws you right in.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.vivianrowe.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Vivian Lopez Rowe</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593715949" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263959" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/ruth-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ruth.jpg" data-orig-size="932,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="ruth" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Kate Riley, &lt;em&gt;Ruth&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Emma Ewbank (Doubleday UK, August) **&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ruth-186x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ruth-636x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263959" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ruth.jpg" alt="" width="932" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ruth.jpg 932w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ruth-186x300.jpg 186w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ruth-636x1024.jpg 636w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ruth-768x1236.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ruth-37x60.jpg 37w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ruth-31x50.jpg 31w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 932px) 100vw, 932px" /></a> Kate Riley, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593715949" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Ruth</a></em>; cover design by Emma Ewbank (Doubleday UK, August)</span>
<p>Simple, elegant and tactile.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jacksmyth.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jack Smyth</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063309777" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263971" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/lihi-lapid-on-her-own/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lihi-Lapid-On-Her-Own.jpg" data-orig-size="996,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Lihi Lapid, On Her Own" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Lihi Lapid, &lt;em&gt;On Her Own&lt;/em&gt; (paperback); cover design by TK TK (HarperVia, April)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lihi-Lapid-On-Her-Own-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lihi-Lapid-On-Her-Own-680x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263971" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lihi-Lapid-On-Her-Own.jpg" alt="" width="996" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lihi-Lapid-On-Her-Own.jpg 996w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lihi-Lapid-On-Her-Own-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lihi-Lapid-On-Her-Own-680x1024.jpg 680w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lihi-Lapid-On-Her-Own-768x1157.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lihi-Lapid-On-Her-Own-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lihi-Lapid-On-Her-Own-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 996px) 100vw, 996px" /></a> Lihi Lapid, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063309777" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>On Her Own</em></a> (paperback); cover design by Olga Grlic (HarperVia, April)</span>
<p>Lush and beautiful Warhol vibes.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.emilymahon.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Emily Mahon</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781641294720" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="246851" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/samrat-upadhyay-darkmotherland/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Samrat-Upadhyay-Darkmotherland-.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Samrat Upadhyay, Darkmotherland" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Samrat Upadhyay, &lt;em&gt;Darkmotherland&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Lauren Peters-Collaer (Soho Press, January)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Samrat-Upadhyay-Darkmotherland--200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Samrat-Upadhyay-Darkmotherland-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-246851" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Samrat-Upadhyay-Darkmotherland-.jpeg" alt="Samrat Upadhyay, Darkmotherland" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Samrat-Upadhyay-Darkmotherland-.jpeg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Samrat-Upadhyay-Darkmotherland--200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Samrat-Upadhyay-Darkmotherland--40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Samrat-Upadhyay-Darkmotherland--33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Samrat Upadhyay, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781641294720" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Darkmotherland</a></em>; cover design by Lauren Peters-Collaer (Soho Press, January)</span>
<p>Such a gorgeous color palette that stopped me in my tracks in the bookstore. The wispy layers and pop of fiery orange hint at danger and unease. Would hang this on my wall!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.mattmakesbooks.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Matt Roeser</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781956046410" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256357" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-13-best-book-covers-of-june-2025/version-1-0-0-50/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91a1rRjsjML.jpg" data-orig-size="1600,2362" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Jacquelyn Zong-Li Ross,&lt;em&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781956046410&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;The Longest Way to Eat a Melon&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Emily Mahon (Sarabande, June 10)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Jacquelyn Zong-Li Ross,&lt;em&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781956046410&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;The Longest Way to Eat a Melon&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Emily Mahon (Sarabande, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91a1rRjsjML-203x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91a1rRjsjML-694x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-256357" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91a1rRjsjML.jpg" alt="Jacquelyn Zong-Li Ross, The Longest Way to Eat a Melon; cover design by Emily Mahon (Sarabande, June 10)" width="1600" height="2362" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91a1rRjsjML.jpg 1600w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91a1rRjsjML-203x300.jpg 203w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91a1rRjsjML-694x1024.jpg 694w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91a1rRjsjML-768x1134.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91a1rRjsjML-41x60.jpg 41w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91a1rRjsjML-1040x1536.jpg 1040w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91a1rRjsjML-1387x2048.jpg 1387w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91a1rRjsjML-34x50.jpg 34w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px" /></a> Jacquelyn Zong-Li Ross,<em> <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781956046410" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Longest Way to Eat a Melon</a></em>; cover design by Emily Mahon (Sarabande, June)</span>
<p>I love this treatment for a long title. And more books should have kittens and/or snails on them.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.morgankrehbiel.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Morgan Krehbiel</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263208" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/the-world-after-rain-by-canisia-lubrin/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/The-World-After-Rain-by-Canisia-Lubrin.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="The World After Rain by Canisia Lubrin" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Canisia Lubrin, &lt;em&gt;The World After Rain&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Jennifer Griffiths (McClelland &#038; Stewart, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/The-World-After-Rain-by-Canisia-Lubrin-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/The-World-After-Rain-by-Canisia-Lubrin-683x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263208" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/The-World-After-Rain-by-Canisia-Lubrin.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/The-World-After-Rain-by-Canisia-Lubrin.jpg 1000w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/The-World-After-Rain-by-Canisia-Lubrin-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/The-World-After-Rain-by-Canisia-Lubrin-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/The-World-After-Rain-by-Canisia-Lubrin-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/The-World-After-Rain-by-Canisia-Lubrin-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/The-World-After-Rain-by-Canisia-Lubrin-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /> Canisia Lubrin, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781593768195" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The World After Rain</em></a>; cover design by Jennifer Griffiths (McClelland &amp; Stewart, October)</span>
<p>Layered blues and falling textures shift in the light, creating a quiet yet enveloping mood that lingers.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://cb-smith.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Coralie Bickford-Smith</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668098684" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255926" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/the-four-spent-the-day-together-9781668098684_hr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-four-spent-the-day-together-9781668098684_hr.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2146" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Chris Kraus, The Four Spent the Day Together" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Chris Kraus, &lt;em&gt;The Four Spent the Day Together&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Alicia Tatone (Scribner, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-four-spent-the-day-together-9781668098684_hr-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-four-spent-the-day-together-9781668098684_hr-668x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-255926" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-four-spent-the-day-together-9781668098684_hr.jpg" alt="Chris Kraus, The Four Spent the Day Together" width="1400" height="2146" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-four-spent-the-day-together-9781668098684_hr.jpg 1400w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-four-spent-the-day-together-9781668098684_hr-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-four-spent-the-day-together-9781668098684_hr-668x1024.jpg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-four-spent-the-day-together-9781668098684_hr-768x1177.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-four-spent-the-day-together-9781668098684_hr-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-four-spent-the-day-together-9781668098684_hr-1002x1536.jpg 1002w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-four-spent-the-day-together-9781668098684_hr-1336x2048.jpg 1336w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-four-spent-the-day-together-9781668098684_hr-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px" /></a> Chris Kraus, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668098684" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Four Spent the Day Together</em></a>; cover design by Alicia Tatone (Scribner, October)</span>
<p>I really like the use of this turquoise spot color in contrast to the flood of neon green of the past couple years. The use of negative space is striking, as is the way these faces are warped and blended together.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://owencorrigan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Owen Corrigan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662601828" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255867" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/91tkepdfscl-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91TKEpDfScL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Melissa Lozada-Oliva, Beyond All Reasonable Doubt, Jesus Is Alive!: Stories" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Melissa Lozada-Oliva, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662601828&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Beyond All Reasonable Doubt, Jesus is Alive!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Luísa Dias (Astra House, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91TKEpDfScL._UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91TKEpDfScL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-255867" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91TKEpDfScL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="Melissa Lozada-Oliva, Beyond All Reasonable Doubt, Jesus Is Alive!: Stories" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91TKEpDfScL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91TKEpDfScL._UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91TKEpDfScL._UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91TKEpDfScL._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Melissa Lozada-Oliva, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662601828" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Beyond All Reasonable Doubt, Jesus is Alive!</a></em>; cover design by Luísa Dias (Astra House, September)</span>
<p>Every time I see this, I see something new.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.keenandesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jamie Keenan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263440" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/9781250374745-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/9781250374745-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="782,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Susan Sontag, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250374745&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;On Photography&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Alex Merto (Picador, April)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Susan Sontag, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250374745&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;On Photography&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Alex Merto (Picador, April)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/9781250374745-copy-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/9781250374745-copy-667x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263440" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/9781250374745-copy.jpg" alt="Susan Sontag, On Photography; cover design by Alex Merto (Picador, April)" width="782" height="1200" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/9781250374745-copy.jpg 782w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/9781250374745-copy-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/9781250374745-copy-667x1024.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/9781250374745-copy-768x1179.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/9781250374745-copy-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/9781250374745-copy-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 782px) 100vw, 782px" /> Susan Sontag, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250374745" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">On Photography</a></em>; cover design by Alex Merto (Picador, April)</span>
<p>The type is so subtly of the era of the book, it’s a beautifully spare and elegant cover. It reminds me of negative canisters.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.tometherington.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Tom Etherington</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="247587" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/harris-lahti-foreclosure-gothic/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Harris-Lahti-Foreclosure-Gothic-.jpeg" data-orig-size="647,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Harris Lahti, Foreclosure Gothic" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Harris Lahti, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602825&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Foreclosure Gothic&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Rodrigo Corral Studio (Astra House, June 10)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Harris-Lahti-Foreclosure-Gothic--194x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Harris-Lahti-Foreclosure-Gothic-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-247587" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Harris-Lahti-Foreclosure-Gothic-.jpeg" alt="Harris Lahti, Foreclosure Gothic" width="647" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Harris-Lahti-Foreclosure-Gothic-.jpeg 647w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Harris-Lahti-Foreclosure-Gothic--194x300.jpeg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Harris-Lahti-Foreclosure-Gothic--39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Harris-Lahti-Foreclosure-Gothic--32x50.jpeg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 647px) 100vw, 647px" /> Harris Lahti, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602825" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Foreclosure Gothic</em></a>; cover design by Adriana Tonello / Rodrigo Corral Studio (Astra House, June)</span>
<p>Deftly brings a sense of unease to an image of American life so mundane it ordinarily passes beneath our notice.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://chasematt.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Matt Chase</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668081440" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255964" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2100" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Erin Somers, The Ten Year Affair" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Erin Somers, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668081440&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Ten Year Affair&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Emily Mahon; cover art by Shannon Cartier Lucy (Simon &amp;amp; Schuster, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-683x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-255964" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr.jpg" alt="Erin Somers, The Ten Year Affair" width="1400" height="2100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr.jpg 1400w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px" /></a> Erin Somers, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668081440" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Ten Year Affair</em></a>; cover design by Emily Mahon; cover art by Shannon Cartier Lucy (Simon &amp; Schuster, October)</span>
<p>I am so intrigued by this cover’s sexy tension in both painting and type!!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.olgagrlic.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Olga Grlic</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668038079" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264052" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/andrew-joseph-white-you-werent-meant-to-be-human/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Andrew-Joseph-White-You-Werent-Meant-to-Be-Human.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Andrew Joseph White, You Weren&#8217;t Meant to Be Human" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Andrew Joseph White, &lt;em&gt;You Weren&#8217;t Meant to Be Human&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Drusilla Adeline (S&#038;S/Saga Press, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Andrew-Joseph-White-You-Werent-Meant-to-Be-Human-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Andrew-Joseph-White-You-Werent-Meant-to-Be-Human-683x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264052" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Andrew-Joseph-White-You-Werent-Meant-to-Be-Human.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Andrew-Joseph-White-You-Werent-Meant-to-Be-Human.jpg 1000w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Andrew-Joseph-White-You-Werent-Meant-to-Be-Human-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Andrew-Joseph-White-You-Werent-Meant-to-Be-Human-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Andrew-Joseph-White-You-Werent-Meant-to-Be-Human-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Andrew-Joseph-White-You-Werent-Meant-to-Be-Human-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Andrew-Joseph-White-You-Werent-Meant-to-Be-Human-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></a> Andrew Joseph White, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668038079" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">You Weren&#8217;t Meant to Be Human</a></em>; cover design by Drusilla Adeline (S&amp;S/Saga Press, September)</span>
<p>So creepy in such a great way, obsessed with the typography and vintage vibes this cover signals.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jamesiacobelli.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">James Iacobelli</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063439948" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264022" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/81vntl0m8sl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81VNTL0m8SL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="975,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="81VNTL0m8SL._SL1500_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Sarah Hall, &lt;em&gt;Helm&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Henry Petrides (Faber &#038; Faber, August)**&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81VNTL0m8SL._SL1500_-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81VNTL0m8SL._SL1500_-666x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264022" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81VNTL0m8SL._SL1500_.jpg" alt="" width="975" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81VNTL0m8SL._SL1500_.jpg 975w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81VNTL0m8SL._SL1500_-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81VNTL0m8SL._SL1500_-666x1024.jpg 666w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81VNTL0m8SL._SL1500_-768x1182.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81VNTL0m8SL._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81VNTL0m8SL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 975px) 100vw, 975px" /></a> Sarah Hall, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063439948" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Helm</a></em>; cover design by Henry Petrides (Faber &amp; Faber, August)</span>
<p>Henry’s cover design for <em>Helm</em> is simple, understated, confident and super evocative. I can really imagine the sensation of the wind on that cover!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kishanrajanidesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kishan Rajani</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781324074410" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="247453" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/lydia-millet-atavists-stories/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Lydia-Millet-Atavists-Stories-.jpeg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Lydia Millet, Atavists- Stories" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Lydia Millet, &lt;em&gt;Atavists: Stories&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Steve Attardo (Norton, April)&lt;/p&gt;
