" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/American-Canto-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/American-Canto-678x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263706" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/American-Canto.jpg" alt="American Canto" width="1400" height="2114" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/American-Canto.jpg 1400w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/American-Canto-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/American-Canto-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/American-Canto-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/American-Canto-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/American-Canto-1017x1536.jpg 1017w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/American-Canto-1356x2048.jpg 1356w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/American-Canto-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px" /></a> Olivia Nuzzi, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668209851" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">American Canto</a></em>; cover design by Alison Forner (Avid Reader Press, December)</span>
<p>Love a clean all type cover.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jayamiceli.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jaya Miceli</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374178710" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255425" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-ultimate-summer-2025-reading-list/attachment/217387674/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/217387674.png" data-orig-size="1010,1186" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="baldwin boggs" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Nicholas Boggs, &lt;em&gt;Baldwin: A Love Story&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by by Rodrigo Corral, photo by David Gahr (FSG, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/217387674-255x300.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/217387674-872x1024.png" class="size-full wp-image-255425" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/217387674.png" alt="baldwin boggs" width="1010" height="1186" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/217387674.png 1010w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/217387674-255x300.png 255w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/217387674-872x1024.png 872w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/217387674-768x902.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/217387674-51x60.png 51w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/217387674-43x50.png 43w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1010px) 100vw, 1010px" /></a> Nicholas Boggs, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374178710" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Baldwin: A Love Story</a></em>; cover design by by Rodrigo Corral, photo by David Gahr (FSG, August)</span>
<p>This macro close-up ultra detailed portrait is a simple and perfect way to show the reader we will be diving into an intimate and honest portrayal that reveals how profoundly James Baldwin&#8217;s personal relationships shaped his life and work.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.nicolecaputo.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Nicole Caputo</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238656" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255792" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/attachment/9780811238656/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780811238656.jpg" data-orig-size="648,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="killing stella" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Marlen Haushofer, tr. Shaun Whiteside, &lt;em&gt;Killing Stella&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Matt Dorfman (New Directions, July)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780811238656-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780811238656.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-255792" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780811238656.jpg" alt="killing stella" width="648" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780811238656.jpg 648w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780811238656-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780811238656-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780811238656-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 648px) 100vw, 648px" /></a> Marlen Haushofer, tr. Shaun Whiteside, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238656" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Killing Stella</a></em>; cover design by Matt Dorfman (New Directions, July)</span>
<p>It must have been difficult to build on the visual language of a cover as stunning as <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811231947" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Wall</a></em>. What a beautiful shade of yellow.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://owencorrigan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Owen Corrigan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374614720" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256282" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/attachment/9780374614720/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780374614720.jpg" data-orig-size="651,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="George Packer, The Emergency" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;George Packer, &lt;em&gt;The Emergency&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Giacomo Girardi (FSG, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780374614720-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780374614720.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-256282" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780374614720.jpg" alt="George Packer, The Emergency" width="651" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780374614720.jpg 651w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780374614720-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780374614720-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780374614720-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 651px) 100vw, 651px" /></a> George Packer, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374614720" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Emergency</a></em>; cover design by Giacomo Girardi (FSG, November)</span>
<p>I really love the design work here. It’s haunting and beautiful, with the face cracking and the vines slowly creeping in.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.luisadias.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Luísa Dias</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593469750" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263960" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/my-beloved-life-design-tom-etherington-973x1500/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/my-beloved-life-design-tom-etherington-973x1500-1.jpeg" data-orig-size="973,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Amitava Kumar, My Beloved Life" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Amitava Kumar, &lt;em&gt;My Beloved Life&lt;/em&gt; (paperback); cover design by Tom Etherington (Vintage, January)&lt;/p&gt;
