<p>The right amount of everything.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.jacksmyth.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jack Smyth</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374617318" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="247569" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/things-in-nature-merely-grow/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Things-in-Nature-Merely-Grow.jpeg" data-orig-size="782,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Things in Nature Merely Grow" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Yiyun Li, &lt;em&gt;Things in Nature Merely Grow&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Na Kim (FSG, May)&lt;/p&gt;
