<p>A simple idea beautifully made.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://bendenzer.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Ben Denzer</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593733400" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264139" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/keith-rosson-coffin-moon/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Keith-Rosson-Coffin-Moon.jpg" data-orig-size="987,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Keith Rosson, Coffin Moon" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Keith Rosson, &lt;em&gt;Coffin Moon&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Aarushi Menon (Random House, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Keith-Rosson-Coffin-Moon-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Keith-Rosson-Coffin-Moon-674x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264139" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Keith-Rosson-Coffin-Moon.jpg" alt="" width="987" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Keith-Rosson-Coffin-Moon.jpg 987w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Keith-Rosson-Coffin-Moon-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Keith-Rosson-Coffin-Moon-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Keith-Rosson-Coffin-Moon-768x1167.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Keith-Rosson-Coffin-Moon-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Keith-Rosson-Coffin-Moon-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 987px) 100vw, 987px" /></a> Keith Rosson, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593733400" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Coffin Moon</a></em>; cover design by Aarushi Menon (Random House, September)</span>
<p>Aarushi pulled off a multi-designer hat trick for author, Keith Rosson, with this cover! Ella Laytham scored the first two goals with the ICONIC covers for <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593595770" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Fever House</a></em> and <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593595800" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Devil By Name</a></em>.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.rachelakedesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Rachel Ake</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263214" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/swallows-uk/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/swallows-uk.jpg" data-orig-size="800,1269" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="swallows uk" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Natsuo Kirino, tr. Lisa Hofmann-Kuroda, &lt;em&gt;Swallows&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Jack Smyth (Canongate, August) **&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/swallows-uk-189x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/swallows-uk-646x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263214" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/swallows-uk.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="1269" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/swallows-uk.jpg 800w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/swallows-uk-189x300.jpg 189w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/swallows-uk-646x1024.jpg 646w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/swallows-uk-768x1218.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/swallows-uk-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/swallows-uk-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /> Natsuo Kirino, tr. Lisa Hofmann-Kuroda, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780307267580" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Swallows</a></em>; cover design by Jack Smyth (Canongate, August)</span>
<p>The opening egg, the type, the color situation, the minimal ornamentation…it’s just perfect.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jaredbartman.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jared Bartman</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781641296267" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="247552" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/paula-bomer-the-stalker/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Paula-Bomer-The-Stalker-.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Paula Bomer, The Stalker" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Paula Bomer, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781641296267&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;The Stalker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Kate Sinclair (Soho Press, May )&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Paula-Bomer-The-Stalker--200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Paula-Bomer-The-Stalker-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-247552" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Paula-Bomer-The-Stalker-.jpeg" alt="Paula Bomer, The Stalker" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Paula-Bomer-The-Stalker-.jpeg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Paula-Bomer-The-Stalker--200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Paula-Bomer-The-Stalker--40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Paula-Bomer-The-Stalker--33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Paula Bomer, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781641296267" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Stalker</a></em>; cover design by Kate Sinclair (Soho Press, May )</span>
<p>I love the pastels shades, pretty boy, nice smile and pleasant typeface and how they contrast with the Terminator 2 hole.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.keenandesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jamie Keenan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263210" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/super-frog-saves-tokyo/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Super-Frog-Saves-Tokyo.jpg" data-orig-size="800,1226" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Super-Frog Saves Tokyo" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Haruki Murakami, &lt;em&gt;Super-Frog Saves Tokyo&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Suzanne Dean (Vintage Books UK, October)**&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Super-Frog-Saves-Tokyo-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Super-Frog-Saves-Tokyo-668x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263210" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Super-Frog-Saves-Tokyo.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="1226" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Super-Frog-Saves-Tokyo.jpg 800w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Super-Frog-Saves-Tokyo-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Super-Frog-Saves-Tokyo-668x1024.jpg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Super-Frog-Saves-Tokyo-768x1177.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Super-Frog-Saves-Tokyo-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Super-Frog-Saves-Tokyo-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /> Haruki Murakami, <em>Super-Frog Saves Tokyo</em>; cover design by Suzanne Dean (Vintage UK, October)</span>
<p>Bright green, delightfully odd, and utterly Murakami.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://cb-smith.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Coralie Bickford-Smith</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668204160" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263969" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/deluxe-hc-edition-of-this-is-how-you-lose-the-time-war-by-by-amal-el-mohtar-max-gladstone/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/deluxe-HC-edition-of-This-Is-How-You-Lose-the-Time-War-by-by-Amal-El-Mohtar-Max-Gladstone.jpg" data-orig-size="1500,1160" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="deluxe HC edition of This Is How You Lose the Time War by by Amal El-Mohtar &#038; Max Gladstone" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Amal El-Mohtar &#038; Max Gladstone, &lt;em&gt;This is How You Lose the Time War&lt;/em&gt; deluxe edition; cover design by Amanda Hudson (S&#038;S/Saga Press, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/deluxe-HC-edition-of-This-Is-How-You-Lose-the-Time-War-by-by-Amal-El-Mohtar-Max-Gladstone-300x232.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/deluxe-HC-edition-of-This-Is-How-You-Lose-the-Time-War-by-by-Amal-El-Mohtar-Max-Gladstone-1240x959.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263969" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/deluxe-HC-edition-of-This-Is-How-You-Lose-the-Time-War-by-by-Amal-El-Mohtar-Max-Gladstone.jpg" alt="" width="1500" height="1160" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/deluxe-HC-edition-of-This-Is-How-You-Lose-the-Time-War-by-by-Amal-El-Mohtar-Max-Gladstone.jpg 1500w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/deluxe-HC-edition-of-This-Is-How-You-Lose-the-Time-War-by-by-Amal-El-Mohtar-Max-Gladstone-300x232.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/deluxe-HC-edition-of-This-Is-How-You-Lose-the-Time-War-by-by-Amal-El-Mohtar-Max-Gladstone-1240x959.jpg 1240w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/deluxe-HC-edition-of-This-Is-How-You-Lose-the-Time-War-by-by-Amal-El-Mohtar-Max-Gladstone-768x594.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/deluxe-HC-edition-of-This-Is-How-You-Lose-the-Time-War-by-by-Amal-El-Mohtar-Max-Gladstone-60x46.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/deluxe-HC-edition-of-This-Is-How-You-Lose-the-Time-War-by-by-Amal-El-Mohtar-Max-Gladstone-50x39.jpg 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" /></a> Amal El-Mohtar &amp; Max Gladstone, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668204160" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">This is How You Lose the Time War</a></em> deluxe edition; cover design by Amanda Hudson (S&amp;S/Saga Press, November)</span>
<p>Masterful elegance for such a long title and two authors! Stunning package!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.olgagrlic.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Olga Grlic</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780393531626" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263672" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/71x-seprirl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71X-sePRIrL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="1004,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="71X-sePRIrL._SL1500_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Arabelle Sicardi, &lt;em&gt;The House of Beauty&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Sarahmay Wilkinson (W. W. Norton, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71X-sePRIrL._SL1500_-201x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71X-sePRIrL._SL1500_-685x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263672" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71X-sePRIrL._SL1500_.jpg" alt="" width="1004" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71X-sePRIrL._SL1500_.jpg 1004w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71X-sePRIrL._SL1500_-201x300.jpg 201w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71X-sePRIrL._SL1500_-685x1024.jpg 685w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71X-sePRIrL._SL1500_-768x1147.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71X-sePRIrL._SL1500_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71X-sePRIrL._SL1500_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1004px) 100vw, 1004px" /></a> Arabelle Sicardi, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780393531626" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The House of Beauty</a></em>; cover design by Sarahmay Wilkinson (W. W. Norton, October)</span>
<p>I love when a printing effect both looks cool AND signals a deeper meaning. The glittery red says both pretty and sparkly but also hints at a sinister feeling of blood, perfectly illustrating the light and dark sides of the beauty industry.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.mattmakesbooks.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Matt Roeser</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263250" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/stop-all-the-clocks-auden/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/stop-all-the-clocks-auden.jpg" data-orig-size="834,1280" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="stop all the clocks auden" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;W.H. Auden, &lt;em&gt;Stop All the Clocks&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Pete Adlington (Faber, November) **&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/stop-all-the-clocks-auden-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/stop-all-the-clocks-auden-667x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263250" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/stop-all-the-clocks-auden.jpg" alt="" width="834" height="1280" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/stop-all-the-clocks-auden.jpg 834w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/stop-all-the-clocks-auden-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/stop-all-the-clocks-auden-667x1024.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/stop-all-the-clocks-auden-768x1179.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/stop-all-the-clocks-auden-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/stop-all-the-clocks-auden-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 834px) 100vw, 834px" /> W.H. Auden, <em>Stop All the Clocks</em>; cover design by Pete Adlington (Faber, November)</span>
<p>This one is giving all of the right vintage vibes. I love the 70s color palette and scratchy hand-lettering.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://sarahschulte.studio/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sarah Schulte</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593803677" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263908" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/notes-to-john-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/notes-to-john.jpg" data-orig-size="987,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="notes to john" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Joan Didion, &lt;em&gt;Notes to John&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by John Gall, photograph by Annie Lebowitz (Knopf, April)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/notes-to-john-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/notes-to-john-674x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263908" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/notes-to-john.jpg" alt="" width="987" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/notes-to-john.jpg 987w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/notes-to-john-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/notes-to-john-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/notes-to-john-768x1167.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/notes-to-john-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/notes-to-john-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 987px) 100vw, 987px" /></a> Joan Didion, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593803677" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Notes to John</em></a>; cover design by John Gall, photograph by Annie Lebowitz (Knopf, April)</span>
<p>The intimacy of this photo is uncomfortable; Didion, not even the focal point, staring at you intensely like the matriarch in your own family who doesn’t want to be photographed. The title and author are set large in a text weight of Didot, echoing the candidness of the photo and the material. It is hard not to consider the meta textual nature of a posthumous work, <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2025/02/05/books/new-book-joan-didion-notes-to-john.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">maybe she is judging us for even picking it up.</a></p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://owencorrigan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Owen Corrigan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063318915" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263961" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/farenehit-182/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Farenehit-182.jpg" data-orig-size="993,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Farenehit-182" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Mark Hoppus, &lt;em&gt;Fahrenheit-182&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Joanne O’Neill (Dey Street Books, April)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Farenehit-182-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Farenehit-182-678x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263961" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Farenehit-182.jpg" alt="" width="993" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Farenehit-182.jpg 993w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Farenehit-182-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Farenehit-182-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Farenehit-182-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Farenehit-182-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Farenehit-182-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 993px) 100vw, 993px" /></a> Mark Hoppus, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063318915" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Fahrenheit-182</em></a>; cover design by Joanne O’Neill (Dey Street Books, April)</span>
<p>My favorite memoir cover this year, I love how the colors and textures are so playful and make it look like a band poster!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://nicoletteseeback.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Nicolette Seeback Ruggiero</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316456241" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="258953" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/amity/amity-3/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/amity.jpg" data-orig-size="1328,2048" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="amity" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Nathan Harris, &lt;em&gt;Amity&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by June Park (Little, Brown, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/amity-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/amity-664x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-258953" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/amity.jpg" alt="amity" width="1328" height="2048" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/amity.jpg 1328w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/amity-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/amity-664x1024.jpg 664w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/amity-768x1184.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/amity-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/amity-996x1536.jpg 996w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/amity-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1328px) 100vw, 1328px" /></a> Nathan Harris, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316456241" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Amity</a></em>; cover design by June Park (Little, Brown, September)</span>
<p>It looks BIG but the type takes up less than half the jacket, which is a real feat. And the colors!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.elizabethyaffe.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Elizabeth Yaffe</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811239356" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263932" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/on-the-clock-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/on-the-clock.jpg" data-orig-size="973,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="on the clock" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Claire Baglin, &lt;em&gt;On the Clock&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Erik Carter (New Directions, March)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/on-the-clock-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/on-the-clock-664x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263932" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/on-the-clock.jpg" alt="" width="973" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/on-the-clock.jpg 973w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/on-the-clock-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/on-the-clock-664x1024.jpg 664w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/on-the-clock-768x1184.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/on-the-clock-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/on-the-clock-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 973px) 100vw, 973px" /></a> Claire Baglin, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811239356" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">On the Clock</a></em>; cover design by Erik Carter (New Directions, March)</span>
<p>Super-sized and super fun.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.stephenbrayda.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Stephen Brayda</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668050460" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="249986" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-18-best-book-covers-of-february/loca-9781668050460_hr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/loca-9781668050460_hr.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2147" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Alejandro Heredia, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668050460&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Loca&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Matt Roeser (Simon &amp;amp; Schuster, February 11)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Alejandro Heredia, &lt;em&gt;Loca&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Matt Roeser (Simon &#038;; Schuster, February)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/loca-9781668050460_hr-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/loca-9781668050460_hr-668x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-249986" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/loca-9781668050460_hr.jpg" alt="Alejandro Heredia, Loca; cover design by Matt Roeser (Simon &amp; Schuster, February 11)" width="1400" height="2147" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/loca-9781668050460_hr.jpg 1400w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/loca-9781668050460_hr-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/loca-9781668050460_hr-668x1024.jpg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/loca-9781668050460_hr-768x1178.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/loca-9781668050460_hr-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/loca-9781668050460_hr-1002x1536.jpg 1002w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/loca-9781668050460_hr-1335x2048.jpg 1335w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/loca-9781668050460_hr-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px" /></a> Alejandro Heredia, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668050460" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Loca</a></em>; cover design by Matt Roeser (Simon &amp; Schuster, February)</span>
<p>Who doesn&#8217;t love a short title that you can exaggerate and make massive on the cover. The pairing of the tall title with the tall tree makes this so&#8230;tall.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="http://notchdesign.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Derek Thornton</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668050521" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264122" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/josh-gad-in-gad-we-trust/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Josh-Gad-In-Gad-We-Trust.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1521" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Josh Gad, In Gad We Trust" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Josh Gad, &lt;em&gt;In Gad We Trust&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by John Vairo Jr. (Gallery Books, January)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Josh-Gad-In-Gad-We-Trust-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Josh-Gad-In-Gad-We-Trust-673x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264122" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Josh-Gad-In-Gad-We-Trust.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="1521" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Josh-Gad-In-Gad-We-Trust.jpg 1000w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Josh-Gad-In-Gad-We-Trust-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Josh-Gad-In-Gad-We-Trust-673x1024.jpg 673w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Josh-Gad-In-Gad-We-Trust-768x1168.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Josh-Gad-In-Gad-We-Trust-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Josh-Gad-In-Gad-We-Trust-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></a> Josh Gad, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668050521" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">In Gad We Trust</a></em>; cover design by John Vairo Jr. (Gallery Books, January)</span>
<p>Designing a cover that involves a full custom photoshoot is a whole different ballgame, and no one does it better than John. Concept, costumes, photographer, posing, execution… it’s a ton of work, and this one came out so great.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://zoenorvell.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Zoe Norvell</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780300276558" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263216" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/rosa-mistika-by-euphrase-kezilahabi/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Rosa-Mistika-by-Euphrase-Kezilahabi.jpg" data-orig-size="645,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Rosa Mistika by Euphrase Kezilahabi" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Euphrase Kezilahabi, tr. Jay Boss Rubin, &lt;em&gt;Rosa Mistika&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Sarah Schulte (Yale University Press, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Rosa-Mistika-by-Euphrase-Kezilahabi-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Rosa-Mistika-by-Euphrase-Kezilahabi.jpg" class="wp-image-263216 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Rosa-Mistika-by-Euphrase-Kezilahabi.jpg" alt="" width="645" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Rosa-Mistika-by-Euphrase-Kezilahabi.jpg 645w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Rosa-Mistika-by-Euphrase-Kezilahabi-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Rosa-Mistika-by-Euphrase-Kezilahabi-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Rosa-Mistika-by-Euphrase-Kezilahabi-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 645px) 100vw, 645px" /></a> Euphrase Kezilahabi, tr. Jay Boss Rubin, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780300276558" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Rosa Mistika</em></a>; cover design by Sarah Schulte (Yale University Press, June)</span>
<p>I just love this illustration and the type layout. It feels fresh and timeless all at once.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jaredbartman.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jared Bartman</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250366382" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255726" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/91hkxz6mjl-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91HKXz6MJL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="652,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Xenobe Purvis, The Hounding" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Xenobe Purvis, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250366382&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Hounding&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; art by Benjamin Cam Norton; cover design by Nicolette Seeback Ruggiero (Henry Holt, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91HKXz6MJL._UF10001000_QL80_-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91HKXz6MJL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-255726" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91HKXz6MJL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="Xenobe Purvis, The Hounding" width="652" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91HKXz6MJL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 652w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91HKXz6MJL._UF10001000_QL80_-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91HKXz6MJL._UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/91HKXz6MJL._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 652px) 100vw, 652px" /></a> Xenobe Purvis, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250366382" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Hounding</em></a>; art by Benjamin Cam Norton; cover design by Nicolette Seeback Ruggiero (Henry Holt, August)</span>
<p>Subtly disorienting. And who could pass by such a good crew of dogs.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://epmock.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Eli Mock</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780385545310" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="247581" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/maria-reva-endling/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Maria-Reva-Endling-.jpeg" data-orig-size="672,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Maria Reva, Endling" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Maria Reva, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780385545310&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Endling&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Emily Mahon, jacket art by Valentin Pavageau (Doubleday, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Maria-Reva-Endling--202x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Maria-Reva-Endling-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-247581" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Maria-Reva-Endling-.jpeg" alt="Maria Reva, Endling" width="672" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Maria-Reva-Endling-.jpeg 672w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Maria-Reva-Endling--202x300.jpeg 202w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Maria-Reva-Endling--40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Maria-Reva-Endling--34x50.jpeg 34w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 672px) 100vw, 672px" /></a> Maria Reva, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780385545310" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Endling</em></a>; cover design by Emily Mahon, jacket art by Valentin Pavageau (Doubleday, June)</span>
<p>Great combination of dancing type and trippy landscape.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.instagram.com/jennycarrow_covers/?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jenny Carrow</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="http://bookshop.org/a/132/9780679723165" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="257163" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/vladimir-nabokovs-entire-backlist-is-getting-a-brand-new-redesign/lolita_final/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Lolita_FINAL.jpg" data-orig-size="1575,2400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Lolita_FINAL" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Vladimir Nabokov, &lt;em&gt;Lolita&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Na Kim (Vintage, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Lolita_FINAL-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Lolita_FINAL-672x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-257163" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Lolita_FINAL.jpg" alt="" width="1575" height="2400" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Lolita_FINAL.jpg 1575w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Lolita_FINAL-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Lolita_FINAL-672x1024.jpg 672w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Lolita_FINAL-768x1170.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Lolita_FINAL-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Lolita_FINAL-1008x1536.jpg 1008w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Lolita_FINAL-1344x2048.jpg 1344w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Lolita_FINAL-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1575px) 100vw, 1575px" /></a> Vladimir Nabokov, <em><a href="http://bookshop.org/a/132/9780679723165" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lolita</a></em>; cover design by Na Kim (Vintage, June)</span>
<p>Damn. So simple but so evocative—it does a lot with very little.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://dana-li.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Dana Li</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250380968" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260299" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/its-okay-but-its-also-really-not-when-dystopian-fiction-is-no-longer-a-thought-experiment/saltcrop/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/saltcrop-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1684,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="saltcrop" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Yume Katasei, &lt;em&gt;Saltcrop&lt;/em; cover design by  Jonathan Bush (Flatiron, September) 
&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/saltcrop-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/saltcrop-674x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-260299" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/saltcrop-scaled.jpg" alt="" width="1684" height="2560" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/saltcrop-scaled.jpg 1684w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/saltcrop-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/saltcrop-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/saltcrop-768x1167.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/saltcrop-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/saltcrop-1011x1536.jpg 1011w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/saltcrop-1347x2048.jpg 1347w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/saltcrop-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1684px) 100vw, 1684px" /></a> Yume Katasei, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250380968" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Saltcrop</em></a>; cover design by Jonathan Bush (Flatiron, September)</span>
<p>So very beautiful and ominously calm!!!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.olgagrlic.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Olga Grlic</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374600334" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="247432" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/andrea-long-chu-authority-essays/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Andrea-Long-Chu-Authority-Essays-.jpeg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Andrea Long Chu, Authority- Essays" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Andrea Long Chu, &lt;em&gt;Authority&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by TK TK (FSG, April)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Andrea-Long-Chu-Authority-Essays--200x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Andrea-Long-Chu-Authority-Essays-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-247432" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Andrea-Long-Chu-Authority-Essays-.jpeg" alt="Andrea Long Chu, Authority- Essays" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Andrea-Long-Chu-Authority-Essays-.jpeg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Andrea-Long-Chu-Authority-Essays--200x300.jpeg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Andrea-Long-Chu-Authority-Essays--40x60.jpeg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Andrea-Long-Chu-Authority-Essays--33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Andrea Long Chu, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374600334" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Authority</a></em>; cover design by Thomas Colligan (FSG, April)</span>
<p>This stunner is exercise in restraint. A win for the less is more crowd. And, a gamble for any book publisher skittish about the fine ornamental lines disappearing when reduced to postage stamp size online. I hope the sales figures for <em>Authority</em> made this elegant jacket solution a success in all ways.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://charlottestrick.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Charlotte Strick</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593302316" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264124" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/rory-power-kill-creatures/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rory-Power-Kill-Creatures.jpg" data-orig-size="900,1360" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Rory Power, Kill Creatures" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Rory Power, &lt;em&gt;Kill Creatures&lt;/em&gt;, cover design by Liz Dresner; illustration by Kei-Ella Loewe (Delacorte, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rory-Power-Kill-Creatures-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rory-Power-Kill-Creatures-678x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264124" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rory-Power-Kill-Creatures.jpg" alt="" width="900" height="1360" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rory-Power-Kill-Creatures.jpg 900w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rory-Power-Kill-Creatures-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rory-Power-Kill-Creatures-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rory-Power-Kill-Creatures-768x1161.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rory-Power-Kill-Creatures-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rory-Power-Kill-Creatures-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /></a> Rory Power, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593302316" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kill Creatures</a></em>, cover design by Liz Dresner; illustration by Kei-Ella Loewe (Delacorte, June)</span>
<p>I just love this incredibly detailed illustration—ever so lovingly created by a human artist (not AI!)</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://zoenorvell.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Zoe Norvell</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263251" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/a-room-above-a-shop/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/a-room-above-a-shop.jpg" data-orig-size="500,765" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="a room above a shop" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Anthony Shapland, &lt;em&gt;A Room Above a Shop&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Tom Etherington (Granta Books, March) **&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/a-room-above-a-shop-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/a-room-above-a-shop.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263251" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/a-room-above-a-shop.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="765" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/a-room-above-a-shop.jpg 500w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/a-room-above-a-shop-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/a-room-above-a-shop-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/a-room-above-a-shop-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /> Anthony Shapland, <em>A Room Above a Shop</em>; cover design by Tom Etherington (Granta Books, March)</span>
<p>I want to frame this cover and hang it on my wall. The delicate tension between the shapes and that particular shade of green are so pleasing to look at.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://sarahschulte.studio/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sarah Schulte</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781982182588" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263888" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/ill-tell-you-when-im-home-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ILL-TELL-YOU-WHEN-IM-HOME.jpg" data-orig-size="988,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="I&#8217;LL TELL YOU WHEN I&#8217;M HOME" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Hala Alyan, &lt;em&gt;I&#8217;ll Tell You When I&#8217;m Home&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by  Zak Tebbal (Avid Reader Press, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ILL-TELL-YOU-WHEN-IM-HOME-198x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ILL-TELL-YOU-WHEN-IM-HOME-674x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263888" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ILL-TELL-YOU-WHEN-IM-HOME.jpg" alt="" width="988" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ILL-TELL-YOU-WHEN-IM-HOME.jpg 988w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ILL-TELL-YOU-WHEN-IM-HOME-198x300.jpg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ILL-TELL-YOU-WHEN-IM-HOME-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ILL-TELL-YOU-WHEN-IM-HOME-768x1166.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ILL-TELL-YOU-WHEN-IM-HOME-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/ILL-TELL-YOU-WHEN-IM-HOME-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 988px) 100vw, 988px" /></a> Hala Alyan, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781982182588" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">I&#8217;ll Tell You When I&#8217;m Home</a></em>; cover design by Zak Tebbal (Avid Reader Press, June)</span>
<p>The plays on scale and proportion here just work so well. It is a book designed to be held in the hand.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.morgankrehbiel.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Morgan Krehbiel</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780674273115" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263952" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/version-1-0-0-65/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Stephanie-Burt-Super-Gay-Poems.jpg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Stephanie Burt, Super Gay Poems" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Stephanie Burt, &lt;em&gt;Super Gay Poems&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Jaya Miceli (Belknap Press, April)&lt;/p&gt;
