<p>I love the interaction of typography with the flourishes. The red vibrates off the page in such a pleasing way.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jamesiacobelli.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">James Iacobelli</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374613358" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="247716" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/something-rotten-andrew-lipstein/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/something-rotten-andrew-lipstein.jpg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="something rotten andrew lipstein" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Andrew Lipstein, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374613358&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Something Rotten&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Na Kim FSG, January)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/something-rotten-andrew-lipstein-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/something-rotten-andrew-lipstein.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-247716" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/something-rotten-andrew-lipstein.jpg" alt="something rotten andrew lipstein" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/something-rotten-andrew-lipstein.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/something-rotten-andrew-lipstein-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/something-rotten-andrew-lipstein-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/something-rotten-andrew-lipstein-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /></a> Andrew Lipstein, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374613358" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Something Rotten</em></a>; cover design by Na Kim FSG, January)</span>
<p>I&#8217;m scared to have kids.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://erikcarter.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Erik Carter</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593712955" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="239021" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2024-part-two/olga-tokarczuk-the-empusium/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Olga-Tokarczuk-The-Empusium.jpeg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Olga Tokarczuk, The Empusium" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Olga Tokarczuk, tr. Antonia Lloyd-Jones, &lt;em&gt;The Empusium&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Lauren Peters-Collaer (Riverhead, September)&lt;/p&gt;
