<p>I’m a big fan of startling colors this year. Voting for the most off kilter palettes in 2025!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.rachelakedesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Rachel Ake</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="256356" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-13-best-book-covers-of-june-2025/61uhgxsvpql-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61UhgXSvpQL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="656,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Antigone Kefala, tr. Madeleine Watts, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9798893380033&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;The Island&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Sarah Schulte (Transit Books, June 3)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Antigone Kefala, tr. Madeleine Watts, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9798893380033&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;The Island&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Sarah Schulte (Transit Books, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61UhgXSvpQL._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61UhgXSvpQL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-256356" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61UhgXSvpQL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="Antigone Kefala, tr. Madeleine Watts, The Island; cover design by Sarah Schulte (Transit Books, June 3)" width="656" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61UhgXSvpQL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 656w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61UhgXSvpQL._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61UhgXSvpQL._UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/61UhgXSvpQL._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 656px) 100vw, 656px" /> Antigone Kefala, tr. Madeleine Watts, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9798893380033" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Island</a></em>; cover design by Sarah Schulte (Transit Books, June)</span>
<p>It reminds me of Mario Degrada’s series of covers for Rizzoli in the 70s.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.tometherington.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Tom Etherington</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063381643" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="249959" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/so-long-to-the-rearview/guatemalan-rhapsody/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Guatemalan-Rhapsody.jpg" data-orig-size="640,966" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Guatemalan Rhapsody" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Jared Lemus, &lt;em&gt;Guatemalan Rhapsody&lt;/em&gt;; cover design and illustration by Vivian Lopez Rowe (Ecco, March)&lt;/p&gt;
