<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.allisonsaltzman.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Allison Saltzman</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263800" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/81adub69opl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81ADUB69OpL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="1041,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="81ADUB69OpL._SL1500_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;David Gentleman, &lt;em&gt;Lessons for Young Artists&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Tom Etherington (Particular Books, July) **&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81ADUB69OpL._SL1500_-208x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81ADUB69OpL._SL1500_-711x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263800" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81ADUB69OpL._SL1500_.jpg" alt="" width="1041" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81ADUB69OpL._SL1500_.jpg 1041w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81ADUB69OpL._SL1500_-208x300.jpg 208w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81ADUB69OpL._SL1500_-711x1024.jpg 711w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81ADUB69OpL._SL1500_-768x1107.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81ADUB69OpL._SL1500_-42x60.jpg 42w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/81ADUB69OpL._SL1500_-35x50.jpg 35w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1041px) 100vw, 1041px" /> David Gentleman, <em>Lessons for Young Artists</em>; cover design by Tom Etherington (Particular Books, July)</span>
<p>A forceful reminder that there’s nowhere to start but at the beginning.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://chasematt.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Matt Chase</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063412101" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264125" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/eleanor-pilcher-thats-what-she-said/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eleanor-Pilcher-Thats-What-She-Said.jpg" data-orig-size="996,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Eleanor Pilcher, That&#8217;s What She Said" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Eleanor Pilcher, &lt;em&gt;That&#8217;s What She Said&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Paul Miele-Herndon (Avon, April)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eleanor-Pilcher-Thats-What-She-Said-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eleanor-Pilcher-Thats-What-She-Said-680x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264125" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eleanor-Pilcher-Thats-What-She-Said.jpg" alt="" width="996" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eleanor-Pilcher-Thats-What-She-Said.jpg 996w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eleanor-Pilcher-Thats-What-She-Said-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eleanor-Pilcher-Thats-What-She-Said-680x1024.jpg 680w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eleanor-Pilcher-Thats-What-She-Said-768x1157.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eleanor-Pilcher-Thats-What-She-Said-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eleanor-Pilcher-Thats-What-She-Said-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 996px) 100vw, 996px" /></a> Eleanor Pilcher, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063412101" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">That&#8217;s What She Said</a></em>; cover design by Paul Miele-Herndon (Avon, April)</span>
<p>In a year where we were spoiled with <span style="text-decoration: underline;">tons</span> of great &#8220;Bento Book&#8221; style covers, this one really nails the look.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://zoenorvell.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Zoe Norvell</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668057032" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="247361" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/sophie-kemp-paradise-logic/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Sophie-Kemp-Paradise-Logic-.jpeg" data-orig-size="663,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Sophie Kemp, Paradise Logic" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Sophie Kemp, &lt;em&gt;Paradise Logic&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by TK TK (Simon &#038; Schuster, March)&lt;/p&gt;
