<p>Look, it’s ludicrous but it&#8217;s fun!!! And knows how to playfully call its audience.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="http://shardurv.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sharanya Durvasula</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780316581332" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="248118" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/lonelycrowds_12_10_d/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/LonelyCrowds_12_10_d-scaled-e1736875232684.jpg" data-orig-size="800,1208" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="LonelyCrowds_12_10_d" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Stephanie Wambugu, &lt;em&gt;Lonely Crowds&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Gregg Kulick (Little, Brown, July)&lt;/p&gt;
