<p>So clever.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.nataliaolbinski.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Natalia Olbinski</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646054039" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263347" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-15-best-book-covers-of-november-2/thingsandthoughts/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/thingsandthoughts.jpg" data-orig-size="776,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Alla Gorbunova, tr. Elina Alter, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646054039&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;(Th)ings and (Th)oughts&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Sarah Schulte (Deep Vellum, November 4)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Alla Gorbunova, tr. Elina Alter, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646054039&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;(Th)ings and (Th)oughts&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Sarah Schulte (Deep Vellum, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/thingsandthoughts-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/thingsandthoughts-662x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263347" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/thingsandthoughts.jpg" alt="Alla Gorbunova, tr. Elina Alter, (Th)ings and (Th)oughts; cover design by Sarah Schulte (Deep Vellum, November 4)" width="776" height="1200" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/thingsandthoughts.jpg 776w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/thingsandthoughts-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/thingsandthoughts-662x1024.jpg 662w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/thingsandthoughts-768x1188.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/thingsandthoughts-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/thingsandthoughts-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 776px) 100vw, 776px" /></a> Alla Gorbunova, tr. Elina Alter, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646054039" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">(Th)ings and (Th)oughts</a></em>; cover design by Sarah Schulte (Deep Vellum, November)</span>
<p>Beautiful illustration and pairing of type.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://epmock.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Eli Mock</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781963270341" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263658" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/only-son-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/only-son.jpg" data-orig-size="1192,1800" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="only son" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Kevin Moffett, &lt;em&gt;Only Son&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Sunra Thompson (McSweeney&#8217;s, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/only-son-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/only-son-678x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263658" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/only-son.jpg" alt="" width="1192" height="1800" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/only-son.jpg 1192w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/only-son-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/only-son-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/only-son-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/only-son-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/only-son-1017x1536.jpg 1017w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/only-son-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1192px) 100vw, 1192px" /></a> Kevin Moffett, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781963270341" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Only Son</a></em>; cover design by Sunra Thompson (McSweeney&#8217;s, November)</span>
<p>The hand drawn illustration and lettering give the cover a warmth that contrasts with the cool tones of the color palette. A high contrast, impactful design.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kimberlyglyder.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kimberly Glyder</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780679775430" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264059" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/haruki-murakami-the-wind-up-bird-chronicle-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haruki-Murakami-The-Wind-Up-Bird-Chronicle-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="778,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Haruki Murakami, The Wind Up Bird Chronicle copy" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Haruki Murakami, &lt;em&gt;The Wind Up Bird Chronicle&lt;/em&gt;, cover design by Henri Campeā; art directed by Megan Wilson (Vintage, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haruki-Murakami-The-Wind-Up-Bird-Chronicle-copy-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haruki-Murakami-The-Wind-Up-Bird-Chronicle-copy-664x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264059" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haruki-Murakami-The-Wind-Up-Bird-Chronicle-copy.jpg" alt="" width="778" height="1200" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haruki-Murakami-The-Wind-Up-Bird-Chronicle-copy.jpg 778w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haruki-Murakami-The-Wind-Up-Bird-Chronicle-copy-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haruki-Murakami-The-Wind-Up-Bird-Chronicle-copy-664x1024.jpg 664w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haruki-Murakami-The-Wind-Up-Bird-Chronicle-copy-768x1185.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haruki-Murakami-The-Wind-Up-Bird-Chronicle-copy-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haruki-Murakami-The-Wind-Up-Bird-Chronicle-copy-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 778px) 100vw, 778px" /></a> Haruki Murakami, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780679775430" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Wind Up Bird Chronicle</a></em>, cover design by Henri Campeā; art directed by Megan Wilson (Vintage, August)</span>
<p>Henri Campeā’s illustrations for these new Murakami designs are pure pleasure.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.markitup.xyz/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mark Abrams</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264126" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/lucy-rose-the-lamb-uk/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lucy-Rose-The-Lamb-UK.jpg" data-orig-size="946,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Lucy Rose, The Lamb UK" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Lucy Rose, &lt;em&gt;The Lamb&lt;/em&gt;, cover design by Dan Jackson (W&#038;N, January)**&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lucy-Rose-The-Lamb-UK-189x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lucy-Rose-The-Lamb-UK-646x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264126" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lucy-Rose-The-Lamb-UK.jpg" alt="" width="946" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lucy-Rose-The-Lamb-UK.jpg 946w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lucy-Rose-The-Lamb-UK-189x300.jpg 189w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lucy-Rose-The-Lamb-UK-646x1024.jpg 646w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lucy-Rose-The-Lamb-UK-768x1218.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lucy-Rose-The-Lamb-UK-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Lucy-Rose-The-Lamb-UK-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 946px) 100vw, 946px" /> Lucy Rose, <em>The Lamb</em>, cover design by Dan Jackson (W&amp;N, January)</span>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://zoenorvell.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Zoe Norvell</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250345271" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263957" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/eli-zuzovsky-mazeltov/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eli-Zuzovsky-Mazeltov-.jpg" data-orig-size="978,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Eli Zuzovsky, Mazeltov" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Eli Zuzovsky, &lt;em&gt;Mazeltov&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by  Emily Mahar (Henry Holt, February)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eli-Zuzovsky-Mazeltov--196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eli-Zuzovsky-Mazeltov--668x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263957" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eli-Zuzovsky-Mazeltov-.jpg" alt="" width="978" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eli-Zuzovsky-Mazeltov-.jpg 978w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eli-Zuzovsky-Mazeltov--196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eli-Zuzovsky-Mazeltov--668x1024.jpg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eli-Zuzovsky-Mazeltov--768x1178.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eli-Zuzovsky-Mazeltov--39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Eli-Zuzovsky-Mazeltov--33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 978px) 100vw, 978px" /></a> Eli Zuzovsky, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250345271" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Mazeltov</a></em>; cover design by Emily Mahar (Henry Holt, February)</span>
<p>Who is this beautiful boy with the blue nose and flower eyes?? This design makes the book feel both literary and commercially viable, which is extraordinarily difficult to pull off.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.alisonforner.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Alison Forner</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374610746" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="247344" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/yuko-tsushima-tr-lisa-hofmann-kuroda-wildcat-dome/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Yuko-Tsushima-tr.-Lisa-Hofmann-Kuroda-Wildcat-Dome-.jpeg" data-orig-size="652,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Yuko Tsushima, tr. Lisa Hofmann-Kuroda, Wildcat Dome" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Yuko Tsushima, tr. Lisa Hofmann-Kuroda, &lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374610746&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Wildcat Dome&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Na Kim (FSG, March 18)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Yuko-Tsushima-tr.-Lisa-Hofmann-Kuroda-Wildcat-Dome--196x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Yuko-Tsushima-tr.-Lisa-Hofmann-Kuroda-Wildcat-Dome-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-247344" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Yuko-Tsushima-tr.-Lisa-Hofmann-Kuroda-Wildcat-Dome-.jpeg" alt="Yuko Tsushima, tr. Lisa Hofmann-Kuroda, Wildcat Dome" width="652" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Yuko-Tsushima-tr.-Lisa-Hofmann-Kuroda-Wildcat-Dome-.jpeg 652w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Yuko-Tsushima-tr.-Lisa-Hofmann-Kuroda-Wildcat-Dome--196x300.jpeg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Yuko-Tsushima-tr.-Lisa-Hofmann-Kuroda-Wildcat-Dome--39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Yuko-Tsushima-tr.-Lisa-Hofmann-Kuroda-Wildcat-Dome--33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 652px) 100vw, 652px" /></a> Yuko Tsushima, tr. Lisa Hofmann-Kuroda, <a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374610746" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Wildcat Dome</em></a>; cover design by Na Kim (FSG, March 18)</span>
<p>I love Na Kim&#8217;s paintings. The type and art work so harmoniously here.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.heaeunhan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Grace Han</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781804298107" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263863" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/fullpage/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/fullpage.jpg" data-orig-size="560,860" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="fullpage" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Seyda Kurt, &lt;em&gt;Hate&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Keith Dodds (Verso, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/fullpage-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/fullpage.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263863" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/fullpage.jpg" alt="" width="560" height="860" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/fullpage.jpg 560w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/fullpage-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/fullpage-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/fullpage-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" /></a> Seyda Kurt, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781804298107" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Hate</a></em>; cover design by Keith Dodds (Verso, November)</span>
<p>Love that they didn&#8217;t use red or black!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.instagram.com/jennycarrow_covers/?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jenny Carrow</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646222896" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264015" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/exhibitionist-mendelsund/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/exhibitionist-mendelsund.jpg" data-orig-size="1353,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="exhibitionist mendelsund" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Peter Mendelsund, &lt;em&gt;Exhibitionist&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Peter Mendelsund (Catapult, June)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/exhibitionist-mendelsund-271x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/exhibitionist-mendelsund-924x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264015" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/exhibitionist-mendelsund.jpg" alt="" width="1353" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/exhibitionist-mendelsund.jpg 1353w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/exhibitionist-mendelsund-271x300.jpg 271w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/exhibitionist-mendelsund-924x1024.jpg 924w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/exhibitionist-mendelsund-768x851.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/exhibitionist-mendelsund-54x60.jpg 54w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/exhibitionist-mendelsund-45x50.jpg 45w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1353px) 100vw, 1353px" /></a> Peter Mendelsund, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646222896" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Exhibitionist</a></em>; cover design by Peter Mendelsund (Catapult, June)</span>
<p>Sometimes the best design is the space between, what isn&#8217;t there, the stencil font, the blank canvas, you get it.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://erikcarter.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Erik Carter</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781963108040" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263909" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/we-contain-landscapes/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/We-Contain-Landscapes-.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="We Contain Landscapes" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Patrycja Humienik, &lt;em&gt;We Contain Landscapes&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Beth Steidle (Tin House, March)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/We-Contain-Landscapes--200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/We-Contain-Landscapes--683x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263909" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/We-Contain-Landscapes-.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/We-Contain-Landscapes-.jpg 1000w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/We-Contain-Landscapes--200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/We-Contain-Landscapes--683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/We-Contain-Landscapes--768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/We-Contain-Landscapes--40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/We-Contain-Landscapes--33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></a> Patrycja Humienik, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781963108040" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">We Contain Landscapes</a></em>; cover design by Beth Steidle (Tin House, March)</span>
<p>I like the way the type brackets the cover, breaking the marbled paper into concentric rectangles. Each rectangle is a new frame, a new landscape, a new poem.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://owencorrigan.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Owen Corrigan</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668068625" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263958" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/kendra-coulter-the-tortoises-tale/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Kendra-Coulter-The-Tortoises-Tale.jpg" data-orig-size="973,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Kendra Coulter, The Tortoise&#8217;s Tale" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Kendra Coulter, &lt;em&gt;The Tortoise&#8217;s Tale&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Alicia Tatone (Simon &#038; Schuster, November)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Kendra-Coulter-The-Tortoises-Tale-195x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Kendra-Coulter-The-Tortoises-Tale-664x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263958" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Kendra-Coulter-The-Tortoises-Tale.jpg" alt="" width="973" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Kendra-Coulter-The-Tortoises-Tale.jpg 973w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Kendra-Coulter-The-Tortoises-Tale-195x300.jpg 195w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Kendra-Coulter-The-Tortoises-Tale-664x1024.jpg 664w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Kendra-Coulter-The-Tortoises-Tale-768x1184.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Kendra-Coulter-The-Tortoises-Tale-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Kendra-Coulter-The-Tortoises-Tale-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 973px) 100vw, 973px" /></a> Kendra Coulter, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668068625" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Tortoise&#8217;s Tale</a></em>; cover design by Alicia Tatone (Simon &amp; Schuster, November)</span>
<p>Gorgeous use of collage.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.laurenpc.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Lauren Peters-Collaer</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662534102" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="263659" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/the-bleeding-woods/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/The-Bleeding-Woods.jpg" data-orig-size="624,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="The Bleeding Woods" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Brittany Amara, &lt;em&gt;The Bleeding Woods&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Caroline Teagle Johnson (47north, October)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/The-Bleeding-Woods-187x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/The-Bleeding-Woods.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-263659" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/The-Bleeding-Woods.jpg" alt="" width="624" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/The-Bleeding-Woods.jpg 624w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/The-Bleeding-Woods-187x300.jpg 187w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/The-Bleeding-Woods-37x60.jpg 37w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/The-Bleeding-Woods-31x50.jpg 31w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 624px) 100vw, 624px" /></a> Brittany Amara, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662534102" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Bleeding Woods</a></em>; cover design by Caroline Teagle Johnson (47north, October)</span>
<p>Upends the clichéd fonts and imagery we typically associate with horror covers. Hauntingly beautiful and creepy at the same time.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kimberlyglyder.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kimberly Glyder</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250329240" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="258734" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-14-best-book-covers-of-august/815somifftl-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/815soMiFfTL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="658,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="emma sloley the island of last things" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Emma Sloley, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250329240&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;The Island of Last Things&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Keith Hayes; art by Jose David Morales (Flatiron, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/815soMiFfTL._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/815soMiFfTL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-258734" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/815soMiFfTL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="emma sloley the island of last things" width="658" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/815soMiFfTL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 658w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/815soMiFfTL._UF10001000_QL80_-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/815soMiFfTL._UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/815soMiFfTL._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 658px) 100vw, 658px" /></a> Emma Sloley, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781250329240" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">The Island of Last Things</a></em>; cover design by Keith Hayes; art by Jose David Morales (Flatiron, August)</span>
<p>Another one that immediately stopped me in the bookstore. The bold, graphic halves of color, those teeth, the tongue! All ready to rip this arm off? Or is it a loving embrace? (My dog does this with my ankles!) I had to know!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.mattmakesbooks.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Matt Roeser</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063388840" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255901" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/9780063388840_1200x1200-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780063388840_1200x1200-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="795,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Jonathan Lethem, A Different Kind of Tension: New and Selected Stories" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Jonathan Lethem, A Different Kind of Tension; cover design and illustration by Kate Dehler (Ecco, September) &lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780063388840_1200x1200-copy-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780063388840_1200x1200-copy-678x1024.jpg" class="wp-image-255901 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780063388840_1200x1200-copy.jpg" alt="Jonathan Lethem, A Different Kind of Tension: New and Selected Stories" width="795" height="1200" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780063388840_1200x1200-copy.jpg 795w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780063388840_1200x1200-copy-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780063388840_1200x1200-copy-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780063388840_1200x1200-copy-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780063388840_1200x1200-copy-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9780063388840_1200x1200-copy-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 795px) 100vw, 795px" /></a> Jonathan Lethem, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780063388840" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>A Different Kind of Tension</em></a>; cover design and illustration by Kate Dehler (Ecco, September)</span>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.allisonsaltzman.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Allison Saltzman</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781786697288" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264057" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/jacek-dukaj-ice/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jacek-Dukaj-Ice.jpg" data-orig-size="987,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Jacek Dukaj Ice" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Jacek Dukaj, tr. Ursula Phillips, &lt;em&gt;Ice&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Yehrin Tong (Head of Zeus/AdAstra, November 6 (ebook))&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jacek-Dukaj-Ice-197x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jacek-Dukaj-Ice-674x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264057" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jacek-Dukaj-Ice.jpg" alt="" width="987" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jacek-Dukaj-Ice.jpg 987w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jacek-Dukaj-Ice-197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jacek-Dukaj-Ice-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jacek-Dukaj-Ice-768x1167.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jacek-Dukaj-Ice-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Jacek-Dukaj-Ice-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 987px) 100vw, 987px" /></a> Jacek Dukaj, tr. Ursula Phillips, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781786697288" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Ice</a></em> (ebook edition); cover design by Yehrin Tong (Head of Zeus/AdAstra, November)</span>
<p>I’m a sucker for black and white covers that should come with a seizure warning. This one is literally and figuratively so sharp, love everything about it!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://jasonarias.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Jason Arias</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781464238208" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264127" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/brian-mcauley-breathe-in-bleed-out/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Brian-McAuley-Breathe-In-Bleed-Out.jpg" data-orig-size="1000,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Brian McAuley, Breathe In, Bleed Out" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Brian McAuley, &lt;em&gt;Breathe In, Bleed Out&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Caitlin Sacks (Poisoned Pen Press, September)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Brian-McAuley-Breathe-In-Bleed-Out-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Brian-McAuley-Breathe-In-Bleed-Out-683x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264127" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Brian-McAuley-Breathe-In-Bleed-Out.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Brian-McAuley-Breathe-In-Bleed-Out.jpg 1000w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Brian-McAuley-Breathe-In-Bleed-Out-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Brian-McAuley-Breathe-In-Bleed-Out-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Brian-McAuley-Breathe-In-Bleed-Out-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Brian-McAuley-Breathe-In-Bleed-Out-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Brian-McAuley-Breathe-In-Bleed-Out-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></a> Brian McAuley, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781464238208" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Breathe In, Bleed Out</em></a>; cover design by Caitlin Sacks (Poisoned Pen Press, September)</span>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://zoenorvell.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Zoe Norvell</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593534915" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264021" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-173-best-book-covers-of-2025/71ezvrnmdtl-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71ezVrNMdTL._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="970,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="71ezVrNMdTL._SL1500_" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Nell Zink, &lt;em&gt;Sister Europe&lt;/em&gt;; cover design and illustration by Josie Staveley Taylor (Viking, April) **&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71ezVrNMdTL._SL1500_-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71ezVrNMdTL._SL1500_-662x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-264021" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71ezVrNMdTL._SL1500_.jpg" alt="" width="970" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71ezVrNMdTL._SL1500_.jpg 970w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71ezVrNMdTL._SL1500_-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71ezVrNMdTL._SL1500_-662x1024.jpg 662w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71ezVrNMdTL._SL1500_-768x1188.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71ezVrNMdTL._SL1500_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/71ezVrNMdTL._SL1500_-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 970px) 100vw, 970px" /></a> Nell Zink, <em>Sister Europe</em>; cover design and illustration by Josie Staveley Taylor (Viking UK, April)</span>
<p>Josie’s design of Sister Europe is rich, playful and stylish—the magpie in me is super drawn to her glimmering illustration and colour choices. It’s a super satisfying cover to look at.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.kishanrajanidesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Kishan Rajani</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593534915" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="247358" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025/nell-zink-sister-europe/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Nell-Zink-Sister-Europe-.jpeg" data-orig-size="658,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Nell Zink, Sister Europe" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Nell Zink, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593534915&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sister Europe&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Linda Huang (Knopf, March 25)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Nell-Zink-Sister-Europe--197x300.jpeg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Nell-Zink-Sister-Europe-.jpeg" class="size-full wp-image-247358" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Nell-Zink-Sister-Europe-.jpeg" alt="Nell Zink, Sister Europe" width="658" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Nell-Zink-Sister-Europe-.jpeg 658w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Nell-Zink-Sister-Europe--197x300.jpeg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Nell-Zink-Sister-Europe--39x60.jpeg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Nell-Zink-Sister-Europe--33x50.jpeg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 658px) 100vw, 658px" /></a> Nell Zink, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593534915" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Sister Europe</a></em>; cover design by Linda Huang (Knopf, March 25)</span>
<p>Great art paired with amazing type!</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.emilymahon.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Emily Mahon</a></em></p>
<span class="caption"><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802164278" class="external" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255722" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/71uf3hi88ul-_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71uF3Hi88UL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="664,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="An Yu, Sunbirth" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;An Yu, &lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802164278&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sunbirth&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Suzanne Dean (Grove, August)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71uF3Hi88UL._UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71uF3Hi88UL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-255722" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71uF3Hi88UL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="An Yu, Sunbirth" width="664" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71uF3Hi88UL._UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 664w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71uF3Hi88UL._UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71uF3Hi88UL._UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/71uF3Hi88UL._UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 664px) 100vw, 664px" /></a> An Yu, <a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802164278" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Sunbirth</em></a>; cover design by Suzanne Dean (Grove, August)</span>
<p>This is instantly eye-catching. The composition and color palette are striking.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>–<a href="https://www.nataliaolbinski.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Natalia Olbinski</a></em></p>
